cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.SY, cs.CV 

The paper discusses the development of a disaster-response system using a mobile manipulation robot and control interfaces. This involves robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for the robot's autonomy, human-computer interaction (cs.HC) for the control interfaces, and systems and control (cs.SY) for the overall system design. Additionally, computer vision (cs.CV) is likely involved in the robot's perception and mapping capabilities.
